  (text "CAN1 safety capture notes:\n- Source traces: PB-100-can1-tx-disable-trace.csv, PB-100-can1-tx-disable.md, PB-100-can1-safety-verification.csv, PB-100-can1-production-dnp-review.csv, PB-100-can1-default-disable-freeze-checklist.csv, PB-100-can1-default-disable-derivation-precheck.csv, PB-100-can1-default-disable-closeout-precheck.csv, PB-100-can1-reset-bench-checklist.csv, PB-100-schematic-net-domain-plan.csv\n- JP_CAN1 is a separate 2-pin DNP/open physical missing-link symbol; no default-populated TX item\n- U_CAN1 is a separate SN74LVC1G125-Q1 DBV 5-pin gate symbol with OE-high disabled polarity\n- CAN1_TX_DISABLED_STATUS remains visible to LB-100 as physical disabled state readback through the reviewed status network\n- PB-BENCH-012 covers reset, unpowered, DNP/open, and disabled-status checks\n- Future vehicle-CAN TX requires a new ADR and explicit hardware action\n\nNo PCB layout from this preliminary capture."
